{"sectionId":708,"sectionIdLiteral":"708","humanId":"lesson-290","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"My present happiness is all I see.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 290"},"annotation":"W-290","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-290\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"708#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Unless I look upon what is not there, my present happiness is all I see.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Eyes that begin to open see at last.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>And I would have Christ‚Äôs vision come to me this very day.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>What I perceive without God‚Äôs Own Correction for the sight I made is frightening and painful to behold.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Yet I would not allow my mind to be deceived by the belief the dream I made is real an instant longer.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>This the day I seek my present happiness, and look on nothing else except the thing I seek.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"708#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>With this resolve I come to You, and ask Your strength to hold me up today, while I but seek to do Your Will.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>You cannot fail to hear me, Father.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>What I ask have You already given me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"708#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And I am sure that I will see my happiness today.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Unless I look upon what is not there, my present happiness is all I see. Eyes that begin to open see at las